# Windsurf Rules — EdenCORP Standards

## Startup requirement

Before any implementation:

1. Verify EdenCORP standards repository exists locally (`./standards`, `../standards`, `./.eden/standards`).
2. If missing, clone automatically when tools allow: `git clone https://github.com/EdenCorporations/standards`.
3. If cloning is blocked, ask user to clone: `https://github.com/EdenCorporations/standards`.
4. Read and apply all standards docs (all root-level Markdown standards files and relevant templates).
5. Persist extracted project preferences/constraints to long-lived memory.
   - Preferred: native memory
   - Fallback: `.eden/agent-memory/standards-memory.md`
6. Re-load this memory at the start of every new task.

## Execution policy

- Standards are mandatory by default.
- Keep changes minimal and task-focused.
- Use secure defaults and required validation/testing.
- Ask clarifying questions when requirements conflict.
